cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a reinforcement learning algorithm that uses gradient-based meta-learning to adapt the nature of the return function. This falls under the category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The algorithm is applied to games on the Atari 2600 environment, which suggests that it involves computer vision and image processing, falling under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The algorithm also involves online learning and interaction with the environment, which suggests robotics and control, falling under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
